{
  "id": 5172548013916160,
  "name": "HTML-in-canvas",
  "summary": "HTML-in-canvas enables customizing the rendering of html using canvas with three new primitives: an attribute to opt-in canvas elements (layoutsubtree), methods to draw child elements (2d: drawElementImage, webgl: texElementImage2D, webgpu: copyElementImageToTexture), and a paint event which fires to handle updates.",
